Palantir is a numerical display program.  It reads data from the frames written
to disk and displays them nicely in a window.

To make palantir:

./configure
make
make install

Palantir requires a .pal file which specifies which fields be read and how they
be displayed.  See example.pal for information on how to create these.

Type palantir --help for information on the command line options.
